President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Sara Gelser and Peggy Sherry to key administration posts. Gelser, a member of the Oregon State House of Representatives, has a background in advocating for individuals with disabilities. She has helped pass legislation on education standards and support systems for adults with developmental disabilities. Sherry, currently the Deputy Chief Financial Officer for the Department of Homeland Security, has experience in financial management and accountability. She has worked with organizations such as the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum and the Government Accountability Office. Gelser and Sherry's nominations reflect President Obama's commitment to appointing experienced and dedicated individuals to important roles in his administration.